'''Rosha Vess''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Homeworld/Legends|from]] the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] who was a member of the [[Zealots of Psusan/Legends|Zealots of Psusan]] cult. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], she was inside the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] on Coruscant with her friends [[Nyrat Agira/Legends|Nyrat Agira]] and [[Immi Danoo]] at the same time as [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] and [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]]. Shortly after, she drank and talked with her friends at the club when Wesell went into the club to [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|hide]] from the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]]. The trio watched as Wesell was disarmed by Kenobi.

==Biography==
Rosha Vess was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Homeworld/Legends|native]] [[Coruscanti/Legends|to]]<ref name="DB" /> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="Complete Locations">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2005)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. She<ref name="DB" /> was a club-hopper alongside her friends [[Nyrat Agira/Legends|Nyrat Agira]] and [[Immi Danoo]]<ref name="SWI752">{{InsiderCite|75|Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night}}</ref> and a member of the [[Zealots of Psusan/Legends|Zealots of Psusan]],<ref name="DB" /> a fast-growing<ref name="Complete Locations" /> female-empowering<ref name="Far Horizons2">''[[Far Horizons]]''</ref> religion fashionable on Coruscant during the last [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="CSWEZealots">{{CSWECite|III|369|Zealots of Psusan}}</ref> In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC Note">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]. The scene from ''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]'' in which [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] is in the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] takes place immediately before the film, therefore meaning it must be set in that [[Standard year/Legends|year]].</ref> Vess and her friends were patrons of the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter">''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]''</ref> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall located in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of Coruscant,<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> at the same time as [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] and [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]]. The two hunters were there preparing to assassinate [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]].<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" />

[[File:FaytonniVessAgira-AOTC.png|thumb|right|300px|Vess and Agira turn to look at Wesell and Kenobi.]]
During a [[Local day/Legends|night]] shortly after,<ref name="NEC Note" /> Vess and her friends were once again in the club, drinking and talking with another Human near the bar when the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] pair of [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] entered. The Jedi were searching for Wesell, who failed to assassinate Amidala earlier that night.<ref name="AOTC" /> The trio's fleeting attention was drawn<ref name="Coruscant Glam">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/explore/attack/2002/10/imageattack20021025.html|series=Image Attack|text=Coruscant Glam}}</ref> by Kenobi as he [[Dismemberment/Legends|cut off]] Wesell's [[Limb/Legends|arm]] when she attempted to ambush him, turning to stare as he did so. Skywalker told the clubgoers to go back to their drinks and the Jedi left with Wesell.<ref name="AOTC" /> 

==Personality and traits==
Vess was friends with Nyrat Agira and Immi Danoo.<ref name="SWI752" /> The cultist was ditzy,<ref name="SWI752" /> had [[Color/Legends|light]] skin, dark [[Hair/Legends|hair]], and a [[Tattoo/Legends|tattoo]] of the Zealots of Psusan's<ref name="DB" /> starburst<ref name="SWI752" /> mark located on her abdomen, the same as Agira's tattoo.<ref name="DB" /> The tattoo advertised her allegiance to the cult.<ref name="SWI752" /> Vess was considered beautiful.<ref name="Coruscant Glam" />

==Equipment==
On the night she visited the Outlander Club<ref name="AOTC" /> in 22 BBY,<ref name="NEC Note 2">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> she had on a black [[Clothing/Legends|top]] with a high collar, a black skirt, and a pair of silver heels.<ref name="AOTC" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|She has adopted the same type of midriff tattoo as Nyrat, advertising her allegiance to the Zealots of Psusan cult &ndash; or at least her willingness to accompany her friend to the body-art parlor.|Daniel Wallace|<ref name="SWI752" />}}
[[File:Faytonni_ep2dvd.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Rosha Vess was portrayed by an uncredited extra (far right).]]
Rosha Vess was created for the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']],<ref name="AOTC" /> which was released on [[May 16]], 2002.<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year by Year: A Visual Chronicle]]''</ref> The Outlander Club scenes including Vess, who was portrayed by an uncredited extra,<ref name="AOTC" /> were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> Prior to the film's release, the character was first pictured in the documentary "[[Making Episode II Webdocs|A Twinkle Beyond Pluto]],"<ref name="ATBP">{{SW|url=video/a-twinkle-beyond-pluto|series=Making Episode II Webdocs|text=Part 5: A Twinkle Beyond Pluto}}</ref> released on [[July 31]], [[2001]].<ref name="ATBP Date">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/me2/archive.html|text=''Making Episode II Webdocs'' archive}}</ref> Vess then first appeared in an illustation in the young readers book ''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]'', written by [[Eric Arnold]], illustrated by [[Valerie Reckert]],<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" /> and released on [[April 23]], [[2002]].<ref name="Amazon">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/young/news20020225.html|text=Book Preview: Episode II Children's Books}}</ref> The image of her in the book was taken from the then upcoming film.<ref name="AOTC" /> 

Vess was first given a name on [[October 25]], 2002, through the [[Image Attack]] feature on [[StarWars.com]].<ref name="Coruscant Glam" /> In the [[April 6]], [[2004]],<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/fanclub/mag/news20040315.html|text=The New Face of Evil}}</ref> article "[[Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night]]," published in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine, author [[Daniel Wallace]] wonders whether Vess has the tattoo only due to her willingness to accompany Agira to get one. Wallace also describes Vess and her friends as the "intergalactic embodiment of the [[Wikipedia:Valley girl|Valley Girl stereotype]]."<ref name="SWI752" />

